### Phase 1: Numerical Modeling & Waveguide Optimization (2036)
* **Milestone 1.1:** Finish finite-difference time-domain (FDTD) simulations of the S-shaped HC-PCW to guarantee zero bending loss for 800 nm signals at a physical length of $4.79668\text{ cm}$.
* **Milestone 1.2:** Simulate the sub-wavelength metamaterial antennas at the 1 µm vacuum gap to optimize resonant photon tunneling while validating a $99.99\%$ reflection coefficient for 30 K infrared blackbody radiation ($\lambda_{\text{max}} \approx 96.6\,\mu\text{m}$).
* **Milestone 1.3:** Complete mathematical modeling of the optical slow-light ring resonators to verify the temporal transformation from 320 ps bus cycles to nanosecond-scale spin-flip windows.

### Phase 2: Material Synthesis & Lithography Proof-of-Concept (2037–2038)
* **Milestone 2.1:** Fabricate 150 nm to 200 nm wide waveguide channels on Thin-Film Lithium Niobate on Sapphire (LNOS) using 193 nm Argon Fluoride Immersion (ArFi) lithography combined with advanced Optical Proximity Correction (OPC).
* **Milestone 2.2:** Execute Atomic Layer Deposition (ALD) of Titanium Dioxide ($\text{TiO}_2$) within the hollow-core channels, followed by in-situ vacuum annealing to achieve the single-crystal rutile phase ($\alpha < 0.001\text{ dB/cm}$).
* **Milestone 2.3:** Verify the anomalous thermal conductivity ($\kappa > 1000\text{ W/mK}$) of the sapphire substrate under simulated 30 K cryo-loads to confirm active hotspot dissipation.

### Phase 3: Heterogeneous 2D Sandwich Prototyping (2039)
* **Milestone 3.1:** Integrate the LNOS electro-optic modulators with the isotopically pure Silicon-28 ($^{28}\text{Si}$) nuclear spin memory matrix on a planar testbed.
* **Milestone 3.2:** Measure the real-world quantum transduction efficiency of flying 800 nm photons into stationary nuclear spins via the slow-light cavity interface.
* **Milestone 3.3:** Test the piezo-metamaterial active suspension system to dynamically stabilize the 1 µm vacuum gap down to sub-nanometer tolerances during thermal drawdown from 300 K to cryo-temperatures.

### Phase 4: Full 3D Stack Integration & Clock Validation (2040)
* **Milestone 4.1:** Finalize the vertical assembly of the 3D Vacuum Sandwich (Layer +1, Layer 0, Layer -1) wrapped in 30 layers of crystalline gold MLI and enclosed in the active OFHC copper shield.
* **Milestone 4.2:** Deploy the system inside a closed-cycle helium pulse-tube cryocooler and verify absolute thermal decoupling (maintaining Layer $\pm1$ at $< 2\text{ K}$ while running Layer 0 at 30 K under full 100 GHz modulation).
* **Milestone 4.3:** Lock the system clock to the native $3.125\text{ GHz}$ grid, achieving deterministic "Data-in-Flight" pipelining with zero structural clock tree overhead and bounded Jitter ($< 2\text{ fs}$).

